description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 37.5 per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exiting opportunity to join a well established respiratory/medical physiotherapy team at Fairfield General Hospital, Bury. In February 2020 Fairfield General Hospital received an overall outstanding rating from CQC and also received an outstanding rating in medical care (including older people&#39;s care).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role would primarily involve treating patients on the Emergency Medical Unit and on the medical wards. It would also involve deputising for the band 7 Team Leader and assisting with the day to day management of the band 5, assistant staff and students. Experience of working within critical care would be complementary to this role and competency in critical care respiratory skills will be valuable for weekend working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to help maintain the outstanding CQC rating, the physiotherapy department are committed to improving quality and productivity. You will gain experience of working in a busy and pro-active environment where evidence based practice in embedded and joint working, service development and CPD is encouraged. This is an ideal opportunity for an experienced band 5 looking to progress in their career or an existing band 6 wanting to gain experience in this dynamic clinical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is ample opportunity to work as part of a very experienced physiotherapy team and as part of the wider multi disciplines line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may be required to work on other Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is working towards a 7 day model of service delivery and as such you will be expected to be flexible in terms of working patterns including weekends, bank holidays and extra hours if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time hours would be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVicky KennedyJob titlePhysiotherapy Operational and Professional LeadEmail addressvicky.kennedy@pat.nhs.ukTelephone number0161 7783513&lt;/p&gt;
